{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3126508,"name":"Isaac Ruben","username":"isaec","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/i/ad7895/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-01-15T01:50:10.508Z","cooked":"<p>The original apriltag demo code that was posted some days ago for photonvision mixed up milliseconds and seconds in the VisionSubsystem. This had me pulling my hair out, so I thought I would share. Earlier today a PR was merged that rearranged this code, so I am not sure if the issue exists anymore. I thought it was worth sharing because it was really unpleasant to debug.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">currentTime - (resultSome.getSecond() / 1000)
// ^ the correct code
currentTime - resultSome.getSecond()
// ^ the original code, confuses the ms result value and the second fpgatime value
</code></pre>
<p>The poseEstimator update value has the milliseconds latency, so you must divide by 1000 before subtracting from the seconds Timer.FPGATime</p>
<p>This issue causes the robot pose to jump backwards after you drive to a position, because you tell the model the frame was taken ~100 seconds ago, instead of 100 milliseconds.</p>
<p>I hope this helps someone and makes any sense, just wanted to get the word out–let me know if this is incoherent.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":4,"updated_at":"2023-01-15T01:50:10.508Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":32,"reads":87,"readers_count":86,"score":207.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":423200,"topic_slug":"original-photonvision-apriltag-code-mixed-up-milliseconds-and-seconds-causing-model-hallucinations","display_username":"Isaac Ruben","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":55829,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/original-photonvision-apriltag-code-mixed-up-milliseconds-and-seconds-causing-model-hallucinations/423200/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3126517,"name":"","username":"mdurrani834","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mdurrani834/{size}/131246_2.png","created_at":"2023-01-15T02:00:04.211Z","cooked":"<p>Yikes…that’s our fault. Sorry for that.</p>
<p>This is fixed in our latest update (release potentially coming soon) where we just give you direct access to the timestamp, so you don’t have to deal with any subtractions and just use it directly.</p>
<p>It is now just this:</p>
<pre><code>    Optional&lt;EstimatedRobotPose&gt; result =
            pcw.getEstimatedGlobalPose(m_poseEstimator.getEstimatedPosition());

    if (result.isPresent()) {
        EstimatedRobotPose camPose = result.get();
        m_poseEstimator.addVisionMeasurement(
                camPose.estimatedPose.toPose2d(), camPose.timestampSeconds);
</code></pre>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":4,"updated_at":"2023-01-15T02:00:04.211Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":80,"readers_count":79,"score":36.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":423200,"topic_slug":"original-photonvision-apriltag-code-mixed-up-milliseconds-and-seconds-causing-model-hallucinations","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":34970,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/original-photonvision-apriltag-code-mixed-up-milliseconds-and-seconds-causing-model-hallucinations/423200/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3126538,"name":"Isaac Ruben","username":"isaec","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/i/ad7895/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-01-15T02:22:19.474Z","cooked":"<p>Sounds great, glad y’all fixed it, just wanted to get the word out in case anyone missed the update–and no worries! Having example code out so fast was a big help.</p>
